# Component Standards

## Purpose

This rule defines how React components are structured, composed, and maintained across the Next.js frontend.

Components must be readable, reusable, accessible, and correctly split between Server and Client boundaries.

---

# Scope

Applies to all `.tsx` files in `apps/web/`.

Covers:

- Component file structure
- Naming and exports
- Props and typing
- shadcn/ui composition
- Server vs Client directives

Does not cover routing, state management, or forms in depth — see dedicated rules.

---

# Component Categories

| Category | Location | Server/Client |
|----------|----------|---------------|
| UI primitives | `components/ui/` | Usually Client (Radix) |
| Shared components | `components/` | Prefer Server |
| Feature components | `features/*/components/` | Mixed |
| Page components | `app/**/page.tsx` | Server |
| Layout components | `app/**/layout.tsx` | Server |

---

# File Structure

Each component file should follow this order:

1. `"use client"` directive (only if required)
2. Imports (React, Next, local, external)
3. Types and interfaces
4. Component function
5. Subcomponents (if small and private)
6. Named export (prefer named over default)

Example skeleton:

```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

interface ProductCardProps {
  title: string;
  price: number;
  className?: string;
}

export function ProductCard({ title, price, className }: ProductCardProps) {
  return (
    <article className={cn("rounded-lg border p-4", className)}>
      <h2 className="text-lg font-semibold">{title}</h2>
      <p className="text-muted-foreground">{price}</p>
    </article>
  );
}
```

---

# Naming Conventions

- Components: PascalCase (`ProductCard`, `CheckoutSummary`)
- Files: match component name (`ProductCard.tsx`)
- Props interface: `{ComponentName}Props`
- Event handlers: `on{Event}` prop, `handle{Event}` internal function
- Boolean props: affirmative names (`disabled`, `isLoading`, not `notEnabled`)

One primary component per file unless subcomponents are truly private implementation details.

---

# Props Design

Rules:

- Prefer explicit props over spreading unknown objects
- Always type props with TypeScript interfaces
- Use `className?: string` for style extension points
- Use `children: React.ReactNode` for composition slots
- Avoid optional props when a sensible default exists
- Document non-obvious props with JSDoc

Forbidden:

- `any` for props
- Prop drilling more than two levels without context or composition
- Passing entire API response objects when only two fields are needed

Prefer picking fields at the data boundary:

```tsx
// Good
<ProductCard title={product.name} price={product.price} />

// Avoid
<ProductCard product={fullProductResponse} />
```

---

# Composition Patterns

Prefer composition over configuration flags.

Good — slot composition:

```tsx
<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <CardTitle>Order Summary</CardTitle>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>{children}</CardContent>
</Card>
```

Avoid — boolean soup:

```tsx
<Card showHeader showFooter variant="order" isCompact />
```

Use compound components from shadcn where available (`Dialog`, `DropdownMenu`, `Form`).

---

# shadcn/ui Integration

Rules:

- Import from `@/components/ui/*`
- Wrap shadcn primitives in feature components; do not re-style primitives globally
- Use `cn()` for merging Tailwind classes
- Use `cva` (class-variance-authority) for variant-heavy custom components
- Keep Radix behavior intact; do not remove focus traps or aria attributes

When adding a new primitive:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
```

Customize via `components.json` theme tokens, not hardcoded hex values in every file.

---

# Server Components

Default for all new components.

Server Components may:

- `async` fetch from FastAPI
- Import server-only modules
- Access cookies and headers via `next/headers`
- Render static HTML without JavaScript cost

Server Components must not:

- Use hooks
- Attach event handlers
- Import client-only libraries

---

# Client Components

Add `"use client"` at the top of the file when required.

Client Components may:

- Use state, effects, and event handlers
- Subscribe to Zustand stores
- Use browser APIs

Keep client components small. Extract static markup into Server Component children where possible:

```tsx
"use client";

export function AddToCartButton({ productId }: { productId: string }) {
  // interactive logic only
}
```

---

# Lists and Keys

- Use stable unique keys (`id` from API), never array index for dynamic lists
- Extract list items into components when rows are non-trivial
- Virtualize long product lists (see `frontend/05-performance-frontend`)

---

# Conditional Rendering

Prefer early returns for loading and error states in Client Components.

In Server Components, use dedicated `loading.tsx` and `error.tsx` at route level when possible.

Avoid nested ternaries beyond one level; extract to named subcomponents or variables.

---

# Accessibility

Every component must:

- Use semantic elements (`button` not `div` for clicks)
- Include `alt` text for images
- Associate labels with inputs
- Preserve shadcn/Radix keyboard behavior
- Not rely on color alone for state

For icon-only buttons:

```tsx
<Button size="icon" aria-label="Remove item">
  <TrashIcon className="h-4 w-4" />
</Button>
```

---

# Performance

- Avoid anonymous inline functions passed to memoized children when measurable
- Use `React.memo` sparingly and only with evidence
- Lazy-load heavy Client Components with `next/dynamic` and a skeleton fallback
- Do not import large libraries in Server Component files that get bundled into client children

---

# Testing Components

- Test behavior and accessibility, not implementation details
- Use Testing Library queries by role and label
- Mock API modules, not fetch globally, in unit tests
- Storybook optional for design system primitives only

---

# Anti-Patterns

Never:

- Create components named `Manager`, `Helper`, or `Wrapper` without clear domain meaning
- Mix data fetching and complex UI in one 500-line file
- Export default and named exports from the same file
- Use `React.FC` with implicit children (prefer explicit props)
- Copy-paste shadcn source instead of installing via CLI
- Put `"use client"` on layout files unnecessarily

---

# Validation Checklist

Before merging component work:

- Correct Server/Client boundary
- Props fully typed, no `any`
- shadcn patterns preserved
- Semantic HTML and aria where needed
- File name matches export
- No unnecessary client JavaScript
- Feature vs shared placement is correct

